üß© Step 1: Understanding the Relational Model

From the image (Relational Model
), we have the following tables and relationships:

Tables:

CUSTOMER

ORDERS

PRODUCT

ORDER_LINE

Relationships:

A CUSTOMER can make many ORDERS ‚Üí CUSTOMER (1) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ< (N) ORDERS

An ORDER can have many PRODUCTS through ORDER_LINE

A PRODUCT can appear in many ORDER_LINE entries
‚Üí many-to-many relationship between ORDERS and PRODUCT via ORDER_LINE

üß± Step 2: SQL Code to Create Tables

Below is the SQL script to create all tables with constraints (based on Oracle SQL syntax, since you use VARCHAR2).

-- 1Ô∏è‚É£ Create CUSTOMER table
CREATE TABLE CUSTOMER (
    CustomerID     NUMBER(6) PRIMARY KEY,
    CustomerName   VARCHAR2(50) NOT NULL,
    CustomerAddress VARCHAR2(100),
    Phone          VARCHAR2(15)
);

-- 2Ô∏è‚É£ Create ORDERS table
CREATE TABLE ORDERS (
    OrderID        NUMBER(6) PRIMARY KEY,
    CustomerID     NUMBER(6),
    CONSTRAINT fk_orders_customer
        FOREIGN KEY (CustomerID)
        REFERENCES CUSTOMER(CustomerID)
);

-- 3Ô∏è‚É£ Create PRODUCT table
CREATE TABLE PRODUCT (
    ProductID      NUMBER(6) PRIMARY KEY,
    ProductName    VARCHAR2(50) NOT NULL,
    Price          NUMBER(10,2) CHECK (Price > 0)
);

-- 4Ô∏è‚É£ Create ORDER_LINE table (associative table)
CREATE TABLE ORDER_LINE (
    OrderID        NUMBER(6),
    ProductID      NUMBER(6),
    Quantity       NUMBER(4) CHECK (Quantity > 0),
    PRIMARY KEY (OrderID, ProductID),
    CONSTRAINT fk_orderline_order
        FOREIGN KEY (OrderID)
        REFERENCES ORDERS(OrderID),
    CONSTRAINT fk_orderline_product
        FOREIGN KEY (ProductID)
        REFERENCES PRODUCT(ProductID)
);

‚öôÔ∏è Step 3: Alter Tables as Requested
‚úÖ 1. Add column Category to PRODUCT
ALTER TABLE PRODUCT
ADD Category VARCHAR2(20);

‚úÖ 2. Add column OrderDate to ORDERS with default value = current system date
ALTER TABLE ORDERS
ADD OrderDate DATE DEFAULT SYSDATE;

üßæ Step 4: Final Check ‚Äî Table Summary
Table	Primary Key	Foreign Keys	Extra
CUSTOMER	CustomerID	‚Äî	‚Äî
ORDERS	OrderID	CustomerID ‚Üí CUSTOMER	OrderDate added
PRODUCT	ProductID	‚Äî	Category added
ORDER_LINE	(OrderID, ProductID)	‚Üí ORDERS, ‚Üí PRODUCT	‚Äî